texts.text: >A horde of demons suddenly surround Lugh and the Liberators.
Yes, originally. Thanks to you lot, I've been disgraced.
We've met before. ...What is the meaning of this?
It's nothing personal, but I've switched employers.
He asked me to take you down since the Liberators suck.
He's none too picky if hirin' Acolytes is his backup plan.
Tch! Better deal with these guys first.
These demons...appear to be the Fomorians.
You slew their King Balor and sent his people underground.
That hatred will, in turn, become a tool for revenge.
>With one swipe of his spear, Lugh slices the demon in half.
Prophecy foretold I would kill him in the future,
and he long feared my birth.
Let me be clear; he was a coward.
>Lugh deftly skewers countless demons with his spear.
Eek! This isn't real! It can't be...
It is futile. You cannot escape the Spear of Assal!
>Lugh shouts an incantation and throws his spear.
>Despite the considerable distance, it pierces Endo's heart.
yet I will not allow a single demon to escape.
We had our hands full, but he's hardly breakin' a sweat.
He is truly Lugh the Omnipotent.
As king, I promise to create a radiant future for this nation.
...You just killed someone right in front of me.
It's not like I knew him or anything, but...
>Ririn and Rika's demon allies charge at Lugh.
>However, Lugh reads their movements and dodges with ease.
Damn. This fight is draggin' on, but he's still rarin' to go.
...Megakin, we may be able to beat Lugh.
For real?! You rock, Jeng Yun!
Regardless, I can only guarantee a tie at best on my own...
Together, we'll take him down and get out alive!
Yes! My life is in your hands!
>Jeng Yun and his demon ally race toward Lugh.
>Jeng Yun and his ally dodge at the last second.
I see...! The spear's advantage is its long reach!
But if you can avoid that, it leaves even Lugh wide open!
>Jeng Yun strikes Lugh's chest at full force.
>Megakin's demon ally bites his spear and intercepts the blow.
>Jeng Yun's vigorous fist throws Lugh back.
Inconceivable. To think a supreme god like me would lose...
I never could have won on my own.
Jeng Yun worked hard to read your movements,
but he needed more than that.
Ririn and Rika bought me enough time to focus.
Uh, maybe don't. It's downright weird, dude.
I'm thrilled too, but let's get him outta here first.
Friends who accept and believe in you... Yes, I see...
I inherited the throne because Nuada had faith in my wit,
Even once I became king, he supported me wholeheartedly.
Looks like we narrowly avoided a coup d'etat.
